land":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bozum","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Danish: habitational name from any of several places whose name means ‘dwelling place on the edge’.","English (North Yorkshire): variant of   Boreham  . Compare   Boram  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Boreham","meanings":["English: habitational name from Boreham (Essex), Boreham Wood in Elstree (Hertfordshire), Boreham Street in Wartling (Sussex), or Boreham in Warminster (Wiltshire). The placenames in Essex, Sussex and Hertfordshire are probably named with Old English <i>bor</i> ‘hill’ + <i>ham</i> ‘homestead’. Compare   Boram   and   Borom  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":8,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Bozum was born in 1374, in Roxton, Bedfordshire, England, his father, John Bozum, was 40 and his mother, Baroness Ida Cornwall, was 35. He married Margaret Arden in 1390, in Roxton, Bedfordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. In 1407, at the age of 33, his occupation is listed as member of parliament in Bedfordshire, England. He died on 10 July 1424, in his hometown, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1374–10 July 1424":"1374–10. juuli 1424","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1374–1424":"1374–1424","1372–1420":"1372–1420","1392–1428":"1392–1428","1394–1460":"1394–1460","1334–1380":"1334–1380","1340–1373":"1340–1373","about 1370":"umbes 1370","ca. 1394":"umbes 1394","1374":"1374","1373":"1373","1340":"1340","1460":"1460","1394":"1394","1372":"1372","1382":"1382","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1424":"1424","1334":"1334","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","after 1373":"pärast 1373","before 1392":"enne 1392","10 July 1424":"10. juuli 1424","1407":"1407","1428":"1428","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","of Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1374–10 July 1424":"1374–10. heinäkuuta 1424","1355–Male":"1355–Kuollut","1374–1424":"1374–1424","1372–1420":"1372–1420","1392–1428":"1392–1428","1394–1460":"1394–1460","1334–1380":"1334–1380","1340–1373":"1340–1373","about 1370":"noin 1370","ca. 1394":"noin 1394","1374":"1374","1373":"1373","1340":"1340","1460":"1460","1394":"1394","1372":"1372","1382":"1382","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","1424":"1424","1334":"1334","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","after 1373":"1373 jälkeen","before 1392":"ennen vuotta 1392","10 July 1424":"10. heinäkuuta 1424","1407":"1407","1428":"1428","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England","Bedfordshire, England":